<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Lord <persName type="from">Pauncefote</persName>
                                    to Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Newport, R. I.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-20"><hi rend="italic">July 20, 1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Rumors current here of message to you from Minister Conger. Is it
                                true; and if so, can you communicate anything for information of my
                                Government?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>